Environment: Google Apps Script (GAS) web app.

Rules:
- Do not use ES module syntax such as `import` or `export`.
- Server-side code must use GAS globals like `HtmlService`, `SpreadsheetApp`, `Session`, `ScriptApp`, and `Utilities`.
- Client-side HTML must call server functions via `google.script.run`.
- Assume templated HTML values use GAS scriptlets like `<?= userEmail ?>`.
- Keep files compatible with Apps Script runtime and browser execution without bundling.
- Spreadsheet column mapping is fixed:
  - A: RP Num
  - D: Market
  - E: User ID
  - F: Issue Type
  - G: Urgency
  - H: Model
  - I: Booth ID
  - J: Color
  - K: Part/Module
  - L: Quantity
  - M: Part RP Code
  - N: Part Description
  - O: Clarifications
  - P: Notes
  - Q: Client
  - R: Address
  - S: Recipient
  - T: Phone
  - U: Email
  - W: Ship Method
  - X: Status
  - Y: Tracking
  - AD: Workshop note (Бележка Цех)
  - AE: Order sent (Изпратена Поръчка) — empty = not sent; date or any value = sent
  - Internal Production U: Order sent (Изпратена Поръчка) for IP rows — same rule
